-/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-   Interactive Element Color — Design Rule (implement with Tailwind)
-   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-
-   RULE: Clickable text, icons, and buttons must NEVER use text-text-muted
-   as their resting color. Use text-text-secondary (2nd deepest) minimum.
-
-   text-text-muted is reserved for:
-   - Truly disabled / non-interactive elements
-   - Placeholder text
-   - Decorative metadata (timestamps, counts, separator dots)
-   - Icons that are purely decorative (not clickable)
-
-   Clickable elements color hierarchy:
-   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
-   │  Resting       → text-text-secondary  (#6B7280)    │
-   │  Hover         → text-text-primary    (#1F2937)    │
-   │  Disabled      → text-text-muted      (#9CA3AF)    │
-   │  Destructive   → hover:text-danger                  │
-   │  Brand link    → text-[var(--color-info)]           │
-   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
-
-   Applies to:
-   - Button labels & icons (ghost, text-only, icon-only)
-   - Menu items (sidebar nav, dropdown items, context menu)
-   - Link text ("View all", "Configure", "Documentation")
-   - Action icons (close X, arrows, settings gear)
-   - Tab labels (inactive tabs)
-   - Disconnect / Remove actions
-
-   Anti-pattern (NEVER do this):
-   ✗ text-text-muted hover:text-text-secondary  ← looks disabled
-   ✓ text-text-secondary hover:text-text-primary ← looks clickable
-
-   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
-
