-   - Position: between sidebar and main, w-[3px] shrink-0 cursor-col-resize
-   - Visual feedback: hover → brand-primary/20, active → brand-primary/40
-   - Hit area: absolute inset-y-0 -left-[2px] -right-[2px] (7px total)
-   - Sidebar width: min 160px, max 320px, default 192px
-   - Main min width: 480px (prevents sidebar from crushing content)
-   - Width persisted to localStorage key "nexu_sidebar_width"
-   - Transition disabled during drag (instant feedback), restored on mouseup
-   - Hidden when sidebar is collapsed
-
-   Sidebar toggle button:
-   - Position: fixed top-[6px] left-[80px] z-50 — next to macOS traffic lights
-   - Size: p-1.5 + 16px icon = 22px total, center ≈ 17px from top
-   - Visually aligned with macOS traffic light center (verified at 6px)
-   - Style: text-tertiary, hover → text-primary + bg-black/5
-   - Icon: PanelLeftClose (expanded) / PanelLeftOpen (collapsed)
-   - NEVER change top/left values — they are pixel-verified for alignment
-
-   Anti-pattern:
-   ✗ flex flex-col lg:flex-row  ← causes sidebar to stack on top at narrow width
-   ✗ lg:hidden / lg:flex        ← responsive show/hide for mobile adaptation
-   ✗ Changing toggle top-[6px]  ← pixel-verified, do not adjust
-   ✓ flex flex-row              ← always horizontal, sidebar always left
-
